<section class="text-block">
  <h3 class="text-block_title">Solution</h3>
  <p class="text-block_copy">The result was bike2go. Our team delivered a highly functional prototype built in native iOS code with a fully functional Node API in less than 2 days. Our app not only allowed users to find bikes and available racks, it tracked ride length, duration, calories, and tons of other statistics. We used this information to provide badges and leaderboards for both friend groups and the city at large.  I worked closely with our developers to provide all UI design, branding, and presentation materials including a landing page. Our team won Overall Best Project and The Dean's Award for Innovation, the two top cash prizes in the hackathon. The application is now available in the <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/bike2go-find-bike-for-indego/id980439330?ls=1&mt=8" target="_blank">App Store</a> for download.</p>
</section>

